subSubSection.paragraph:
Trochanteral organ with 11–14 smooth spiny chaetae; seven to nine in the arms of “L” and three to five between them (
Figure 2F
). Inner differentiated tibiotarsal chaetae “smooth” with ciliations closely appressed to axis, the most distal one smooth on hind tibiotarsus; inner outstanding macrochaetae located at about one-third of distance from base, ciliate and tapered (
Figure 2G
). Unguis with one inner distal tooth and a pair of basal unequal teeth, the outer one larger. Unguiculus with outer edge serrate (three or four teeth). Tenent hair pointed, subequal to unguiculus (
Figure 2H
).

Abd. IV 2.5 times as long as Abd. III along dorsal midline. Abd. I with four macrochaetae centrally (m2–4, m4p) and two S-chaetae laterally. Abd. II with three central (a2, m3, m3e), one lateral (m5) macrochaetae and two S-chaetae. Abd. III with one central (m3), three lateral (amp, pm6, p6) macrochaetae and two S-chaetae (
Figure 2I
). Abd. IV with six central (A3, A6, C1, B4–6), six lateral macrochaetae and about 12 S-chaetae on each side (
Figure 2J
). Abd. V with about 32 chaetae and three S-chaetae on each side; macrochaetae m2, m3 and m5 always much larger than others (
Figure 2K
). Tenaculum with 4 + 4 teeth and one large striate chaeta (
Figure 2L
). Ventral tube anteriorly with five or six ciliate chaetae on each side (
Figure 2M
); posteriorly with six smooth chaetae; each lateral flap with eight smooth chaetae (
Figure. 2N
). Manubrium with 3 + 3 dorsal smooth chaetae; 1 + 1 on base of dens (
Figure 2O
). Manubrial plaque with two pseudopores and two ciliate chaetae (
Figure 2P
). Distal smooth part of dens 1.2–1.5 as long as mucro. Mucro falcate and basal spine long, its tip reaching the tip of apical tooth (
Figure 2Q
).
